William C. Griffiths: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 23, 2017 5:17 PM ET
Building Products

Company Overview of Quanex Building Products Corporation



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
William C. Griffiths  Chairman of the Board, Chief Executive Officer and President, Quanex Building Products CorporationAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships65$3,830,565As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. William C. Griffiths, also known as Bill, has been the Chairman, Chief Executive Officer and President at Quanex Building Products Corporation since July 09, 2013. Mr. Griffiths served as a Consultant at Champion Enterprises Holdings, LLC and served as its Chief Executive Officer and President until June 2010. Mr. Griffiths also served as the President and Chief Executive Officer of Champion Enterprises Inc. from August 1, 2004 to March 19, 2010. Mr. Griffiths served ... as President of CSMI Inc. and President and Chief Executive Officer of Cygnus Industries Inc. He served as President of Fluid Systems businesses of SPX Corp. from May 2001 to July 31, 2004. From September 1998 to May 2001, he served as President of the Fluid Systems Division of United Dominion Industries Ltd. He joined United Dominion Industries Ltd. in July 1994 as President of Waukesha Cherry-Burrell from 1994 to 1998 and also served as its Senior Vice President. He served as President of United Dominion's Waukesha Cherry-Burrell unit in Delavan, Wisconsin. From 1975 to 1994, Mr. Griffiths served in a variety of mostly senior executive positions at Admac Inc., the Jarvis Clark Company, Tamrock Inc., Ingersoll-Rand and Anglo American Corp. He has thirty years of business experience in line management roles, including international experience. He served as the Chairman of Champion Enterprises Inc. from March 2006 to March 19, 2010 and its Director from August 1, 2004 to March 19, 2010. He has been a Director of Quanex Building Products Corporation since February 2009. He served as Director of Wolverine Tube Inc. from October 19, 2005 to March 24, 2008. He holds a BS with Honors in Mining Engineering from the University of London.Read Full Background




